<br>
Also, if you have a suprise encounter your best 'knee-jerk' reaction is not to try to run away, but instead turn into the enemy and attack full bore, giving it everything you have right from the start. If you are killed, chances are you were dead anyway regardless of if you tried to run or not. Charging them at first sight is really your best chance, particularly if they got the drop on you and have already launched a ranged attack. Just about the only exception would be if you have a larger force or a friendly keep very close at hand... then you might have a shot at making it on the run and either luring the enemy into the main force or escaping under cover of the NPC guards. This stands true for rezers, as well. Even if you manage to get away and your group is killed all you are is bait for a solo kill when you try to get close enough to rez. Better to attack and everyone /release and regroup at the castle if the enemy is too strong to kill. Charging a sprung ambush or a suprised enemy is a tried and true combat tactic.<br>
